comments: Booker (PHX) cuts toward the perimeter and incidental contact occurs to Tucker's (MIL) face as he disengages off-ball.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
As they approach the pick, Connaughton (MIL) and Crowder (PHX) engage and disengage, causing marginal contact to occur during the defensive switch.
Connaughton (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position during Booker's (PHX) drive and contact to Booker's hand or wrist after the release is incidental.
Bridges (PHX) moves laterally into Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path on the drive and affects his SQBR.
Middleton (MIL) extends his arms into Bridges (PHX) and dislodges him from his position off-ball.
Bridges (PHX) places a hand to Antetokounmpo's (MIL) body as he turns around him and slides it off.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) cleanly blocks Ayton's (PHX) play at the basket.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is established in Crowder's (PHX) path before the contact. He extends somewhat as they separate.
Before Middleton (MIL) gathers the ball, Crowder (PHX) brushes his arm without affecting his ability to gather.
Crowder (PHX) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt. Middleton returns to the ground and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Crowder as he starts to backpedal up court.
Paul (PHX) clamps Holiday's (MIL) right arm, affecting his ability to bring two hands to the ball during the rebound.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is in Crowder's (PHX) path before the contact occurs, and Crowder goes over the pick and maintains his defensive positioning.
Paul (PHX) starts to lose control of his dribble before reaching Antetokounmpo (MIL). Antetokounmpo has his arm extended and there is marginal contact to Paul's chest as Paul is losing his balance.
Booker (PHX) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact created by Middleton (MIL) during his play at the basket.
Tucker (MIL) maintains a legal forearm to Booker's (PHX) side during his drive.
Johnson (PHX) makes contact to Middleton's (MIL) arm and the contact dislodges the ball.
Tucker (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position on Booker's (PHX) drive.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) releases his inbounds pass while he still has a foot on the court.
Johnson (PHX) and Paul's (PHX) contact to Middleton (MIL) after he receives the ball in the corner is marginal and a foul call was not warranted.
Johnson (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Tucker's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Paul (PHX) holds Holiday's (MIL) arm, affecting his SQBR.
